xt-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I do not wish to imply that as a result of the write down of assets, commercial suppliers of the system components delivered were poor performing or dysfunctional technology, quite the contrary, I have been made aware that a number of these components were delivered to the specification the BBC had commissioned however their performance was governed by the overall vision of the technology system which was controlled by the corporation.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I consider that faced with a project that had failed to meet benefits expectations for the second time Lord Hall was left with no other option than to shut down DMI to remove the corporation from further risks created by the technology and cultural challenges of the project.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I had not referred to this in my written evidence as I did not believe that this would be a matter of debate.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">3 February 2014</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>